    "plan_content": "Here's the implementation plan for the `ollama rename` feature. It touches **5 files** with ~80 lines of new code, all following existing patterns exactly:\n\n---\n\n### Files changed\n\n| File | What's added |\n|------|-------------|\n| `api/types.go` | `RenameRequest` struct (after `CopyRequest`, line 765) |\n| `api/client.go` | `Client.Rename()` POST to `/api/rename` (after `Copy()`, line 387) |\n| `server/images.go` | `RenameModel()` = `CopyModel` + `m.Remove()` (after `CopyModel`, line 434) |\n| `server/routes.go` | `RenameHandler()` method + `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", ...)` route (after `CopyHandler`, line 1483) |\n| `cmd/cmd.go` | `RenameHandler` func + `renameCmd` cobra command + registrations (after `CopyHandler`/`deleteCmd`) |\n\n---\n\n### Key design decisions\n\n- **`RenameModel` = `CopyModel` + `m.Remove()`** — reuses the existing copy logic verbatim, then removes only the *manifest* file via `manifest.Remove()`. It deliberately does **not** call `RemoveLayers()`, because the blobs are still referenced by the newly-created destination manifest.\n- **404 check** — calls `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)`; if `errors.Is(err, os.ErrNotExist)` → 404.\n- **409 check** — calls `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)`; if `err == nil` (destination already readable) → 409 Conflict.\n- **CLI command** uses `cobra.ExactArgs(2)` and `checkServerHeartbeat`, matching the `cp` command pattern exactly.",
